Overplotting

Notes: - SOme points are spread out. - Some are stacked on top of each other. - Use alpha parameter 1/20 -> It will take 20 points to be equivalent of one data point. - Age is a continuous variable, but in the graph it appears to be.. To add the effect of continuity, use jitter to add noise. Observe the difference.

What do you notice in the plot?

Response: - The bulk of users have really have friend counts less than 1000.

Coord_trans()

Notes: - To get a better visualisation of the data, limit y axis

What do you notice?

  • Easier to see the friend count.
  • Cant use jitter directly. Some people have 0 friend count. They would have imaginary values after sqrt application. TO add jitter use geom_point(position = position_jitter())

Correlation

Notes: - Summarise the strength of ther elationship using a single number. - Use pearson_product relation coefficient - Rule of thumb: - |correlation| > 0.3 is meaningful but small - |correlation| > 0.5 is moderate - |correlation| > 0.7 is pretty large

with(pf, cor.test(age, friend_count, method='pearson'))
